1
00:00:13,433 --> 00:00:14,600
My gosh, Colby.

2
00:00:14,667 --> 00:00:15,900
Why did you let him get drunk?

3
00:00:15,967 --> 00:00:18,633
You know he can't handle
alcohol.

4
00:00:18,700 --> 00:00:21,133
Do you come here to save me
from my misery?

5
00:00:21,200 --> 00:00:22,633
What are you talking about?

6
00:00:22,700 --> 00:00:25,133
I'm so hurting right now.

7
00:00:25,200 --> 00:00:27,400
I thought you would tell her
the truth.

8
00:00:27,467 --> 00:00:29,833
I don't want my mom to worry.

9
00:00:29,900 --> 00:00:32,833
Even if we stay away
from each other,

10
00:00:32,900 --> 00:00:37,333
my mom will still be bothered
that Red and I know each other.

11
00:00:37,433 --> 00:00:39,233
About Amanda...

12
00:00:39,300 --> 00:00:40,567
What about Amanda?

13
00:00:40,633 --> 00:00:42,033
I already know the truth.

14
00:00:42,100 --> 00:00:43,733
What's the truth?

15
00:00:43,800 --> 00:00:45,200
Red, Red.

16
00:00:45,267 --> 00:00:48,733
Our son is getting affected
by your conflict with Amanda.

17
00:00:48,800 --> 00:00:52,900
He saw how the two of you fight.

18
00:00:52,967 --> 00:00:55,967
Red is all we have, Rina.

19
00:00:56,033 --> 00:00:57,367
Mom. Dad...

20
00:00:57,433 --> 00:01:00,233
Is it true that Amanda's
daughter was there

21
00:01:00,300 --> 00:01:01,967
when the crime happened?

22
00:01:02,033 --> 00:01:03,733
Aren't you mistaken?

23
00:01:03,800 --> 00:01:06,733
What if you put someone
innocent in jail?

24
00:01:06,800 --> 00:01:08,300
Where are all these questions
coming from?

25
00:01:08,400 --> 00:01:09,900
What are you trying to say?

26
00:01:09,967 --> 00:01:11,733
That we're making up stories?

27
00:01:11,800 --> 00:01:13,100
I deserve to know the truth.
Right?

28
00:01:13,167 --> 00:01:14,867
Why was she imprisoned?

29
00:01:14,933 --> 00:01:18,533
The case was expedited.

30
00:01:18,600 --> 00:01:23,967
I don't know how Atty. Gualvez
was able to close the case

31
00:01:24,033 --> 00:01:27,767
and have Amanda jailed.

32
00:01:27,833 --> 00:01:29,467
I will pay whatever the cost,
Attorney.

33
00:01:29,533 --> 00:01:31,667
We did that before, didn't we?

34
00:01:31,733 --> 00:01:33,700
So, it's true?

35
00:01:33,767 --> 00:01:35,267
You don't have to tell me that

36
00:01:35,333 --> 00:01:37,233
because I know
my mom is innocent.

37
00:01:37,300 --> 00:01:39,967
Yen, I've realized everything
only now.

38
00:01:40,033 --> 00:01:42,167
But can you change anything?

39
00:01:47,500 --> 00:01:51,267
Our families are still enemies.

40
00:01:51,333 --> 00:01:53,767
Yen...

41
00:01:53,833 --> 00:01:58,133
Isn't that enough reason to stop
whatever we have?

42
00:01:58,200 --> 00:02:01,667
Why do you let our families
affect you?

43
00:02:01,733 --> 00:02:03,267
Why don't we just choose
for ourselves?

44
00:02:03,333 --> 00:02:06,300
And not for our families.

45
00:02:06,367 --> 00:02:08,567
Yen, I still love you.

46
00:02:08,633 --> 00:02:12,800
I hope our love for each other
overcome everything.

47
00:02:12,867 --> 00:02:13,867
Sorry, Red.

48
00:02:13,967 --> 00:02:15,700
But I don't want us to ruin
our relationship

49
00:02:15,767 --> 00:02:18,600
with our families
by being selfish...

50
00:02:18,667 --> 00:02:20,800
by choosing ourselves over them.

51
00:02:22,000 --> 00:02:23,700
Go back to your family, Red.

52
00:02:23,767 --> 00:02:24,900
Sorry.

53
00:02:31,433 --> 00:02:32,333
Yen!

54
00:02:45,067 --> 00:02:47,000
Red! Red, are you okay?

55
00:02:47,100 --> 00:02:48,033
Help! Help!

56
00:02:48,100 --> 00:02:49,967
Let's bring my friend
to the hospital!

57
00:02:50,033 --> 00:02:54,833
Red!

58
00:02:54,900 --> 00:02:56,033
We need to go to the hospital.

59
00:02:56,100 --> 00:02:57,767
Yen, I'm okay.

60
00:02:57,833 --> 00:02:59,567
Please call a taxi.

61
00:02:59,633 --> 00:03:00,767
Taxi!

62
00:03:02,433 --> 00:03:03,733
Lift him up, please.

63
00:03:03,800 --> 00:03:04,833
Help, please.

64
00:03:04,900 --> 00:03:06,200
Red.

65
00:03:10,600 --> 00:03:13,167
Come on. Pick up, Red.

66
00:03:13,233 --> 00:03:16,333
Why aren't you answering
my calls?

67
00:03:20,700 --> 00:03:23,367
This is your fault, Amanda!

68
00:03:23,467 --> 00:03:28,900
You're a pest who keeps ruining
our family!

69
00:03:28,967 --> 00:03:31,267
You took Angelo away from me.

70
00:03:31,333 --> 00:03:33,200
And now you're taking Red too.

71
00:03:34,900 --> 00:03:36,933
You're such a pest!

72
00:03:37,000 --> 00:03:41,267
Outrageous!

73
00:03:41,333 --> 00:03:42,900
Shameless!

74
00:03:49,567 --> 00:03:54,100
Ma'am, there's a delivery
from your personal shopper.

75
00:03:54,200 --> 00:03:55,467
Are you okay, Ma'am?

76
00:03:55,533 --> 00:03:57,267
Do I look okay?

77
00:03:57,333 --> 00:03:58,433
Do I?

78
00:03:58,500 --> 00:04:00,033
What do you need?

79
00:04:00,100 --> 00:04:02,833
Is there anything I can do
to calm you down?

80
00:04:02,900 --> 00:04:05,033
I want Amanda gone!

81
00:04:05,100 --> 00:04:06,467
Can you do that?

82
00:04:06,533 --> 00:04:09,100
If you can't, get your face
out of here

83
00:04:09,167 --> 00:04:11,300
if you want to keep your job!

84
00:04:11,367 --> 00:04:12,467
Get out!

85
00:04:16,600 --> 00:04:17,800
Sab!

86
00:04:17,867 --> 00:04:19,167
It's Red!

87
00:04:19,233 --> 00:04:21,233
- Something happened to Red.
- What?

88
00:04:21,300 --> 00:04:23,633
He got into an accident
with that girl.

89
00:04:23,700 --> 00:04:25,500
- Where are they?
- They're outside the campus.

90
00:04:25,567 --> 00:04:27,167
Okay, hurry up!
Let's go to them.

91
00:04:34,267 --> 00:04:36,633
Eden!

92
00:04:36,700 --> 00:04:37,767
Raichu.

93
00:04:37,833 --> 00:04:39,267
What happened?

94
00:04:39,333 --> 00:04:40,267
What happened?

95
00:04:40,333 --> 00:04:42,400
Red was hit by a motorcycle.

96
00:04:42,467 --> 00:04:43,433
What?

97
00:04:43,500 --> 00:04:44,467
Let me go with you.

98
00:04:44,533 --> 00:04:45,733
No need.

99
00:04:45,800 --> 00:04:48,333
Just tell my mom and Aunt
that I'll be coming home late.

100
00:04:48,400 --> 00:04:49,633
But don't tell them
I'm with Red.

101
00:04:49,700 --> 00:04:51,700
I'll just bring him to Everwell
Hospital.

102
00:04:51,767 --> 00:04:53,067
Keep me updated.

103
00:04:53,133 --> 00:04:54,600
- Be safe.
- Okay.

104
00:04:58,300 --> 00:05:00,000
Red! Red!

105
00:05:00,067 --> 00:05:02,433
Where's Red?

106
00:05:02,533 --> 00:05:03,533
Raichu!

107
00:05:03,600 --> 00:05:05,200
Where the hell is Red?

108
00:05:09,833 --> 00:05:12,267
That girl is such a pest!

109
00:05:12,333 --> 00:05:13,900
Where's Red?

110
00:05:19,300 --> 00:05:21,367
Oh, Sabina. Thank goodness.

111
00:05:21,433 --> 00:05:25,633
Yes. Sabina, thank you
for calling.

112
00:05:25,700 --> 00:05:26,700
Is Red there with you?

113
00:05:26,767 --> 00:05:27,900
Are you together?

114
00:05:27,967 --> 00:05:29,633
Auntie, please don't panic.

115
00:05:29,700 --> 00:05:32,300
Something happened to Red.

116
00:05:32,367 --> 00:05:34,267
What happened?

117
00:05:34,367 --> 00:05:35,467
He got into an accident.

118
00:05:35,533 --> 00:05:37,067
He was brought to the hospital.

119
00:05:39,133 --> 00:05:40,700
Which hospital?

120
00:05:40,767 --> 00:05:42,133
Everwell Hospital, Auntie.

121
00:05:42,200 --> 00:05:44,667
The one near our school.

122
00:05:44,733 --> 00:05:45,633
I'm on my way there.

123
00:05:45,700 --> 00:05:47,933
I'll just meet you there.

124
00:05:58,900 --> 00:06:00,167
Raichu, Raichu!

125
00:06:00,233 --> 00:06:02,933
Raichu! Are you going home now?

126
00:06:03,000 --> 00:06:04,067
Yes, Auntie.

127
00:06:04,133 --> 00:06:07,533
Is Eden not going home with you?

128
00:06:07,600 --> 00:06:10,733
I think she still has a meeting,
Auntie.

129
00:06:10,833 --> 00:06:13,200
My timing is perfect.

130
00:06:13,267 --> 00:06:14,767
We can go home together.

131
00:06:14,833 --> 00:06:17,067
I'll wait for her.

132
00:06:17,133 --> 00:06:19,500
I think their meeting
will take a long time.

133
00:06:19,567 --> 00:06:21,933
You'll get bored waiting,
Auntie. You should go home.

134
00:06:22,000 --> 00:06:23,167
No, it's okay.

135
00:06:23,233 --> 00:06:29,433
We agreed that if I have time,
I'll come by the school.

136
00:06:29,500 --> 00:06:34,467
I'm worried Rina might also do
something to her,

137
00:06:34,533 --> 00:06:39,033
especially since her son
is also enrolled here.

138
00:06:39,100 --> 00:06:41,833
Right?

139
00:06:41,933 --> 00:06:43,467
What if I wait inside?

140
00:06:43,533 --> 00:06:45,800
Where is their meeting?

141
00:06:45,867 --> 00:06:50,400
Auntie, she's in a meeting.

142
00:06:50,467 --> 00:06:51,800
I know.

143
00:06:51,867 --> 00:06:56,900
Eden is not here.

144
00:06:56,967 --> 00:06:59,067
She's at the hospital.

145
00:06:59,133 --> 00:07:00,067
What?

146
00:07:00,133 --> 00:07:01,467
She's at the hospital?

147
00:07:01,533 --> 00:07:03,600
Why? What happened?

148
00:07:03,667 --> 00:07:05,400
Nothing happened to her, Auntie.

149
00:07:05,467 --> 00:07:07,800
Raichu, which hospital
did she go to?

150
00:07:07,867 --> 00:07:09,167
Tell me!

151
00:07:09,233 --> 00:07:11,000
Which hospital? I'm going to see
my daughter.

152
00:07:11,067 --> 00:07:12,567
Auntie!

153
00:07:13,433 --> 00:07:16,567
Red, hang in there.
We're almost at the hospital.

154
00:07:16,667 --> 00:07:18,933
Why did you have to follow me?

155
00:07:19,000 --> 00:07:22,233
You wouldn't have gotten in an
accident if you didn't do that.

156
00:07:22,300 --> 00:07:26,367
When your family finds out about
this, they will hate me more.

157
00:07:27,733 --> 00:07:29,000
Yenyen.

158
00:07:31,033 --> 00:07:32,700
Sorry, I'll stop blaming you.

159
00:07:32,767 --> 00:07:34,333
I'll just keep quiet.

160
00:07:40,467 --> 00:07:41,600
Red.

161
00:07:44,067 --> 00:07:45,067
Red?

162
00:07:49,667 --> 00:07:50,667
Red.

163
00:07:50,733 --> 00:07:52,533
Red, open your eyes.

164
00:07:52,600 --> 00:07:53,800
Red.

165
00:07:53,867 --> 00:07:57,933
Red, wake up.

166
00:07:58,000 --> 00:08:00,133
Keep your eyes on him.

167
00:08:00,200 --> 00:08:01,733
Don't let him go.

168
00:08:01,800 --> 00:08:04,367
I myself will collect
what he owes us.

169
00:08:05,867 --> 00:08:09,367
Zandro, can we talk?

170
00:08:12,700 --> 00:08:14,633
I know we're not okay.

171
00:08:14,700 --> 00:08:16,867
That we're not close.

172
00:08:16,933 --> 00:08:21,000
But can you please do me
a favor, this time?

173
00:08:21,100 --> 00:08:22,700
What is it about?

174
00:08:22,767 --> 00:08:25,567
It's about your sister's
plans for Amanda.

175
00:08:28,933 --> 00:08:31,600
Can you stop tolerating her?

176
00:08:35,533 --> 00:08:38,567
I don't like how Amanda
interferes with our lives,

177
00:08:38,633 --> 00:08:41,467
especially what she did to Red.

178
00:08:41,533 --> 00:08:43,267
But nothing will come out good

179
00:08:43,333 --> 00:08:48,600
if your sister continues
to bother Amanda.

180
00:08:48,667 --> 00:08:50,500
It's just going to be a vicious
cycle.

181
00:08:50,567 --> 00:08:52,700
It will happen again and again.

182
00:08:54,700 --> 00:08:58,900
Victor, you know my sister.

183
00:08:58,967 --> 00:09:00,900
You can't say no to her.

184
00:09:00,967 --> 00:09:04,533
She has her own mind.
So you can't control her.

185
00:09:04,600 --> 00:09:08,467
If I say no to her,
she'll get mad at me.

186
00:09:08,533 --> 00:09:10,700
You can talk to her, can't you?

187
00:09:10,767 --> 00:09:12,133
Or you can refuse her.

188
00:09:12,200 --> 00:09:16,433
Or you can convince her to stop.

189
00:09:16,500 --> 00:09:21,967
Victor, if you as her husband
cannot control her,

190
00:09:22,033 --> 00:09:23,400
what more if it's me?

191
00:09:26,033 --> 00:09:28,133
Victor!

192
00:09:28,233 --> 00:09:30,933
Victor! Something happened
to Red.

193
00:09:31,000 --> 00:09:32,667
What?

194
00:09:32,733 --> 00:09:34,467
Something happened to Red.

195
00:09:34,533 --> 00:09:36,467
We need to go to the hospital.

196
00:09:36,533 --> 00:09:38,000
Come on. Let's go.

197
00:09:41,567 --> 00:09:42,700
Sorry.

198
00:09:42,767 --> 00:09:45,367
If I only talked to you,
this wouldn't have happened.

199
00:09:48,067 --> 00:09:52,533
Red, I won't forgive myself
if something happens to you.

200
00:09:52,600 --> 00:09:55,300
Red, wake up, please.

201
00:09:55,367 --> 00:09:57,567
I'm going to talk to you.

202
00:09:57,633 --> 00:10:00,533
I will listen to everything you
have to say.

203
00:10:00,600 --> 00:10:03,267
Just wake up.

204
00:10:03,367 --> 00:10:04,900
Red.

205
00:10:04,967 --> 00:10:09,033
Red, I will put everything
aside for now.

206
00:10:09,100 --> 00:10:10,733
Red, wake up.

207
00:10:12,367 --> 00:10:14,100
I don't want to lose you.

208
00:10:16,667 --> 00:10:20,267
Even if I'm driving you away...

209
00:10:20,333 --> 00:10:24,200
even if I'm avoiding you...

210
00:10:24,267 --> 00:10:26,600
I still love you.

211
00:10:29,933 --> 00:10:31,000
Red...

212
00:10:31,067 --> 00:10:33,033
Red, wake up, please.

213
00:10:35,833 --> 00:10:41,933
Red, no matter how hard
I deny my feelings,

214
00:10:44,867 --> 00:10:49,267
My heart is saying that I still
love you.

215
00:10:57,333 --> 00:10:58,867
Really?

216
00:10:58,933 --> 00:11:00,900
You still love me?

217
00:11:04,567 --> 00:11:06,600
So, you're okay?

218
00:11:06,667 --> 00:11:09,200
Did you just fool me?

219
00:11:09,300 --> 00:11:11,967
Well. Yes, I'm okay.

220
00:11:12,033 --> 00:11:14,233
Nothing's wrong with me.
My arm just hurts a little.

221
00:11:14,300 --> 00:11:16,567
What?

222
00:11:16,633 --> 00:11:17,900
Sorry, Yen.

223
00:11:17,967 --> 00:11:22,567
That's the only way I could
think of to talk to you.

224
00:11:22,633 --> 00:11:26,667
That's also the only way to know
if you still like me...

225
00:11:26,733 --> 00:11:28,733
if you still love me.

226
00:11:28,800 --> 00:11:31,167
And I'm right.

227
00:11:31,233 --> 00:11:32,933
Please, don't get mad at me.

228
00:11:33,000 --> 00:11:35,333
I can't lose you.

229
00:11:35,400 --> 00:11:38,100
We can't erase
our families' past,

230
00:11:38,167 --> 00:11:40,633
but we can overcome it.

231
00:11:40,700 --> 00:11:43,867
Especially after everything
I've learned.

232
00:11:43,967 --> 00:11:46,367
We can find out the truth
together.

233
00:11:46,433 --> 00:11:47,733
Just don't give up on us.

234
00:11:47,800 --> 00:11:48,967
Please.

235
00:11:53,167 --> 00:11:54,200
So, what do you think?

236
00:11:55,300 --> 00:11:58,700
I keep on talking, but you
haven't said a word yet.

237
00:11:58,767 --> 00:12:00,433
Do you want to know my answer?

238
00:12:02,667 --> 00:12:05,067
Mister, can you pull over?

239
00:12:05,133 --> 00:12:06,533
And please bring this man
to the hospital

240
00:12:06,600 --> 00:12:08,133
and have his head checked.

241
00:12:08,200 --> 00:12:09,367
Yen, talk to me first.

242
00:12:09,433 --> 00:12:10,833
Don't get off the car.

243
00:12:10,900 --> 00:12:12,167
Let's talk.

244
00:12:12,233 --> 00:12:14,633
Yen!

245
00:12:14,733 --> 00:12:16,067
Hang on, Mister.

246
00:12:19,667 --> 00:12:22,433
Hon, I'll park in the basement.

247
00:12:22,500 --> 00:12:23,800
All right. Don't take too long,
okay?

248
00:12:23,867 --> 00:12:25,133
Okay.

249
00:12:42,300 --> 00:12:44,967
Unbelievable. You again?

250
00:12:45,033 --> 00:12:49,633
You're the one who keeps
following me.

251
00:12:49,733 --> 00:12:51,767
Me following you?

252
00:12:51,833 --> 00:12:56,300
You're the one who keeps showing
yourself to me.

253
00:12:56,367 --> 00:12:59,967
You're like a magnet.

254
00:13:00,033 --> 00:13:01,400
You keep sticking with us.

255
00:13:01,467 --> 00:13:02,433
- Me?
- Yes.

256
00:13:02,500 --> 00:13:04,167
- I stick with you?
- Yeah.

257
00:13:04,233 --> 00:13:05,167
I don't do that.

258
00:13:05,233 --> 00:13:07,500
I don't want to catch
your bad attitude.

259
00:13:07,567 --> 00:13:08,567
You're like a yo-yo .

260
00:13:08,633 --> 00:13:10,200
No matter how often
I throw you out,

261
00:13:10,267 --> 00:13:12,400
you keep coming back.

262
00:13:12,467 --> 00:13:17,400
If you're not sticking with me,
you stick with my son.

263
00:13:17,467 --> 00:13:18,967
Why? What are you trying
to prove?

264
00:13:19,033 --> 00:13:20,800
That you're innocent?

265
00:13:20,900 --> 00:13:21,833
Pitiful?

266
00:13:21,900 --> 00:13:22,967
I'm not saying anything
to your son.

267
00:13:23,033 --> 00:13:24,333
If there's anything
I have to say,

268
00:13:24,400 --> 00:13:25,933
I will only tell him the truth.

269
00:13:26,000 --> 00:13:28,400
I won't waste my time on you.
I'm tired of you.

270
00:13:28,467 --> 00:13:31,500
I'm just here to ask
about my daughter.

271
00:13:31,567 --> 00:13:32,833
Auntie!

272
00:13:32,900 --> 00:13:36,833
Oh. Sab.

273
00:13:36,900 --> 00:13:38,333
- Sab!
- I'm so sorry.

274
00:13:38,400 --> 00:13:40,000
I cannot find Red.

275
00:13:40,067 --> 00:13:43,633
I've already checked the
reception and emergency rooms,

276
00:13:43,700 --> 00:13:46,633
but they said there's no
Roderick Ramos confined here.

277
00:13:46,700 --> 00:13:49,067
Maybe you got
the wrong hospital.

278
00:13:49,133 --> 00:13:50,300
Auntie, that's impossible.

279
00:13:50,367 --> 00:13:53,733
Everyone who saw them said
they went here.

280
00:13:53,800 --> 00:13:56,933
And Everwell is the only
hospital near the school.

281
00:13:57,033 --> 00:13:58,433
So, explain to me.

282
00:13:58,500 --> 00:14:00,033
Where's Red? Where is he?

283
00:14:00,100 --> 00:14:01,800
I don't really know.

284
00:14:10,733 --> 00:14:12,533
Will you keep on walking
until you get home?

285
00:14:12,600 --> 00:14:13,733
What's your plan?

286
00:14:13,800 --> 00:14:15,433
It's none of your business.

287
00:14:15,500 --> 00:14:17,367
Why don't you take care
of your wound?

288
00:14:17,433 --> 00:14:18,500
You're so stubborn.

289
00:14:18,567 --> 00:14:20,133
Stop following me.

290
00:14:20,200 --> 00:14:21,533
I'm okay, Yen!

291
00:14:21,600 --> 00:14:23,200
You know who's not okay?

292
00:14:23,267 --> 00:14:24,267
Us!

293
00:14:24,333 --> 00:14:29,700
We need emergency intervention.

294
00:14:29,800 --> 00:14:31,533
You almost died earlier,

295
00:14:31,600 --> 00:14:33,600
and you still had the guts
to pull a prank.

296
00:14:33,667 --> 00:14:37,633
You said you'd talk to me
if I woke up.

297
00:14:37,700 --> 00:14:41,033
You're the one who's kidding.
You didn't keep your word.

298
00:14:41,100 --> 00:14:42,833
Yen! Come on!

299
00:14:42,900 --> 00:14:44,500
I kept my word.

300
00:14:44,567 --> 00:14:46,967
I listened to your
long monologue.

301
00:14:47,033 --> 00:14:49,233
And I even gave you an answer.

302
00:14:49,300 --> 00:14:50,900
What's not clear about that?

303
00:14:50,967 --> 00:14:52,100
Everything!

304
00:14:52,167 --> 00:14:54,433
This is not clear to me.

305
00:14:54,500 --> 00:14:56,500
You told me you still love me,
didn't you?

306
00:14:56,567 --> 00:14:57,633
I told you about our problems.

307
00:14:57,700 --> 00:14:58,867
I even gave you solutions.

308
00:14:58,933 --> 00:15:01,133
But it seems nothing to you.

309
00:15:01,200 --> 00:15:02,867
Now, Yenyen, tell me.

310
00:15:02,967 --> 00:15:05,267
How can we give
this love a chance

311
00:15:05,333 --> 00:15:07,167
if you won't give us a chance?

312
00:15:11,200 --> 00:15:14,800
Are you sure there's no
Eden Sta. Maria here?

313
00:15:14,867 --> 00:15:17,233
She really is not here.

314
00:15:21,700 --> 00:15:23,667
What's with your face?

315
00:15:23,733 --> 00:15:26,333
You look so upset.

316
00:15:26,400 --> 00:15:30,233
You said you're looking
for your daughter,

317
00:15:30,300 --> 00:15:32,733
so I hope she's in a grave
condition.

318
00:15:32,800 --> 00:15:34,000
Or better yet,

319
00:15:34,067 --> 00:15:36,767
I hope she's now with Angelo,
my son whom you murdered.

320
00:15:36,867 --> 00:15:39,467
So that way, I can get even
with you.

321
00:15:41,100 --> 00:15:43,000
Really?

322
00:15:43,067 --> 00:15:44,167
Won't you really stop?

323
00:15:44,233 --> 00:15:46,900
- My God, Auntie!
- Keep my daughter out of it!

324
00:15:46,967 --> 00:15:50,600
I will accept every insult
you give me.

325
00:15:50,667 --> 00:15:56,133
But I will not let you say
anything about my daughter!

326
00:15:56,200 --> 00:15:59,200
You're such a monster!

327
00:15:59,267 --> 00:16:01,033
What? Does it hurt, Amanda?

328
00:16:01,100 --> 00:16:02,900
Yes, it hurts to lose a child.

329
00:16:02,967 --> 00:16:06,400
And I want you
to experience it too!

330
00:16:06,467 --> 00:16:10,100
Here. That's what you deserve!

331
00:16:10,200 --> 00:16:16,700
You cannot cleanse your soul no
matter how much alcohol you use!

332
00:16:16,767 --> 00:16:17,833
What now?

333
00:16:17,900 --> 00:16:19,167
You'll still fight?

334
00:16:19,233 --> 00:16:20,267
Oh my God! Auntie!

335
00:16:22,000 --> 00:16:23,933
Auntie! Stop it!

336
00:16:24,000 --> 00:16:25,567
Stop it!

337
00:16:31,267 --> 00:16:34,000
Raichu, why didn't you go
with my sister?

338
00:16:34,067 --> 00:16:36,633
I'm sure it will be trouble
again once she sees Eden

339
00:16:36,700 --> 00:16:39,367
with Rina's son!

340
00:16:39,433 --> 00:16:41,267
I can't do anything.

341
00:16:41,367 --> 00:16:43,133
I got scared.

342
00:16:43,200 --> 00:16:45,900
I didn't even get to explain
why Eden was in the hospital.

343
00:16:45,967 --> 00:16:49,500
She left right after I told her
which hospital Eden was in.

344
00:16:49,567 --> 00:16:52,033
Let's just pray that Amanda
and Rina won't see each other.

345
00:16:52,100 --> 00:16:55,533
I'm sure it will end up
in a fight.

346
00:16:55,600 --> 00:16:57,633
I'll call her.

347
00:17:02,933 --> 00:17:04,067
She's not picking up.

348
00:17:09,700 --> 00:17:11,933
My gosh!

349
00:17:12,000 --> 00:17:13,000
My God.

350
00:17:19,667 --> 00:17:20,833
Can anybody help us?

351
00:17:20,900 --> 00:17:25,333
Please! Call security!

352
00:17:25,400 --> 00:17:27,733
Please stop!

353
00:17:27,800 --> 00:17:29,067
Auntie!

354
00:17:29,133 --> 00:17:39,100
Security!

355
00:17:41,767 --> 00:17:43,200
Rina!

356
00:17:43,267 --> 00:17:44,933
Hey!

357
00:17:45,000 --> 00:17:46,167
Mister, help us! Hurry!

358
00:17:46,233 --> 00:17:47,233
- Ma'am, that's enough!
- Rina!

359
00:17:47,300 --> 00:17:48,733
Stop it, you two!

360
00:17:48,833 --> 00:17:51,133
Get that woman!

361
00:17:51,200 --> 00:17:52,667
Get her!

362
00:17:52,733 --> 00:17:54,467
Why me?

363
00:17:54,533 --> 00:17:55,767
Amanda, please!

364
00:17:55,833 --> 00:18:00,267
Why me? I didn't plan on wasting
my time fighting with your wife!

365
00:18:00,333 --> 00:18:02,533
She started it! I was just
looking for my daughter!

366
00:18:02,600 --> 00:18:05,000
But your wife asked for trouble.

367
00:18:05,067 --> 00:18:09,100
So I gave it to her!

368
00:18:09,167 --> 00:18:10,500
You monsters!

369
00:18:13,100 --> 00:18:14,100
Get out of here!

370
00:18:14,167 --> 00:18:15,267
Leave!

371
00:18:15,333 --> 00:18:16,900
Is this place yours?

372
00:18:16,967 --> 00:18:20,833
- Monster!
- Do you own this place?

373
00:18:20,900 --> 00:18:22,133
How dare she!

374
00:18:22,233 --> 00:18:23,900
How dare she, Victor.

375
00:18:23,967 --> 00:18:25,633
How dare she!

376
00:18:31,133 --> 00:18:33,133
I will get you next time,
Amanda.

377
00:18:33,200 --> 00:18:34,300
I will get back at you.

378
00:18:34,367 --> 00:18:35,633
That's enough.

379
00:18:37,433 --> 00:18:38,833
See?

380
00:18:38,900 --> 00:18:40,767
You can't say a thing
because you know deep inside

381
00:18:40,833 --> 00:18:43,067
that you still have feelings
for me.

382
00:18:43,133 --> 00:18:44,600
Just leave me alone.

383
00:18:44,667 --> 00:18:48,800
Aren't you tired of forcing
something impossible to happen?

384
00:18:48,867 --> 00:18:50,633
Why would I get tired?

385
00:18:50,700 --> 00:18:53,200
We're not doing anything wrong.

386
00:18:53,267 --> 00:18:55,067
Nothing is impossible, Yenyen.

387
00:18:55,167 --> 00:18:59,167
We just have to believe that
we can change our situation.

388
00:19:06,533 --> 00:19:07,967
Red, what are you going to do?

389
00:19:08,900 --> 00:19:10,000
Get back down!

390
00:19:10,067 --> 00:19:11,667
What are you going to do?

391
00:19:14,100 --> 00:19:16,333
I won't move until you talk
to me.

392
00:19:16,400 --> 00:19:17,367
Red, get back down.

393
00:19:17,433 --> 00:19:18,800
It's dangerous.

394
00:19:20,400 --> 00:19:21,567
Red, get back down!

395
00:19:21,633 --> 00:19:22,733
You're so stubborn!

396
00:19:22,800 --> 00:19:24,433
So you really don't care
about me?

397
00:19:26,900 --> 00:19:30,033
What's with you, Red? Stop it!

398
00:20:11,700 --> 00:20:13,833
What's with you, Red? Stop it!

399
00:20:43,000 --> 00:20:45,200
You just made your decision.

400
00:20:45,267 --> 00:20:47,167
I'll hold on to it.

401
00:20:47,233 --> 00:20:48,767
I won't let go.

402
00:20:55,100 --> 00:20:58,500
Why did you do that? You know
you can fall from there!

403
00:20:58,567 --> 00:21:01,133
That's called trust fall.

404
00:21:01,200 --> 00:21:04,767
I just trusted my feelings
that you wouldn't let go of me.

405
00:21:04,833 --> 00:21:07,633
And you did just that.

406
00:21:07,700 --> 00:21:10,300
I was right, Yen.

407
00:21:31,233 --> 00:21:33,667
I'm just so happy.

408
00:21:33,733 --> 00:21:36,100
I thought I'd never
see you again.

409
00:21:36,167 --> 00:21:37,433
I missed you.

410
00:21:39,533 --> 00:21:41,600
Who would have thought that,
on this bridge,

411
00:21:41,700 --> 00:21:42,800
we'd be connected again?

412
00:21:48,667 --> 00:21:51,467
I don't know what to feel, Red.

413
00:21:51,533 --> 00:21:52,633
I wanted to be happy

414
00:21:52,700 --> 00:21:55,400
because I followed
what my heart was saying.

415
00:21:55,467 --> 00:21:57,167
But is it right for us
to be happy

416
00:21:57,233 --> 00:22:00,000
while our parents are in misery?

417
00:22:00,067 --> 00:22:03,000
It's not going to be easy.

418
00:22:03,067 --> 00:22:05,733
For our parents,
everything is wrong.

419
00:22:08,100 --> 00:22:12,033
But I thought of a way to make
this right to their eyes.

420
00:22:12,100 --> 00:22:14,333
What are we going to do?

421
00:22:14,400 --> 00:22:17,467
We'll keep it from them for now.

422
00:22:17,567 --> 00:22:23,100
We'll find the perfect timing.

423
00:22:23,167 --> 00:22:28,733
When everything is already okay,
when they have already healed...

424
00:22:28,800 --> 00:22:30,400
we can tell them about it.

425
00:22:33,767 --> 00:22:38,333
Yen, would you like to continue
this journey with me?

426
00:23:16,433 --> 00:23:20,900
Honestly, Auntie, Yenyen is a
bad influence on Red.

427
00:23:20,967 --> 00:23:23,700
Even when we were still
on the island,

428
00:23:23,800 --> 00:23:28,900
Red often got harmed
because of her.

429
00:23:28,967 --> 00:23:30,600
Who is that Yenyen?

430
00:23:30,667 --> 00:23:32,733
I went to the hospital
that Raichu told me about,

431
00:23:32,800 --> 00:23:33,700
but you weren't there.

432
00:23:33,767 --> 00:23:35,033
I'm okay, Mom.

433
00:23:35,100 --> 00:23:37,367
I just accompanied a friend.

434
00:23:37,433 --> 00:23:39,867
So why did you have to keep it
from me?

435
00:23:39,933 --> 00:23:43,733
And why did Raichu have to lie
that you were in a meeting?

436
00:23:43,800 --> 00:23:44,733
What?

437
00:23:44,800 --> 00:23:48,433
Red, I cannot control
your feelings, okay?

438
00:23:48,500 --> 00:23:52,033
You are old enough to decide
who you want.

439
00:23:52,100 --> 00:23:54,133
Just be honest with me.

440
00:23:54,200 --> 00:24:00,433
Now tell me, what is so special
about this Yenyen girl?

441
00:24:00,533 --> 00:24:04,067
This is your chance to tell me
the truth.
